name: Bakugan
overview: Follow the adventures of Dan Kouzo and his best friends: the first kids on Earth to bond with the mysterious creatures known as Bakugan!

seasons.name: Battle Planet
seasons.overview: Dan Kouzo and his pals bond with mysterious creatures known as Bakugan while fighting sinister forces out to control the world.

seasons.name: Geogan Rising
seasons.overview: The Awesome Brawlers band together to fight off a powerful enemy determined to break the bond between Earth and Vestroia, the Bakugan's home planet.

seasons.name: Evolutions
seasons.overview: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan heroes take battling to the next level as Vestroia's elemental powers spread strange energy on Earth.

episodes.name: Origin of the Species (1)
episodes.overview: Dan meets his partner Bakugan Drago for the first time and we learn about the incident that happened on Earth twelve years ago.

episodes.name: Origin of the Species (2)
episodes.overview: Dan and friends win the Bakugan Battle, firmly establishing the Awesome Ones as our heroes and Bakugan Brawlers.

episodes.name: Burger Run
episodes.overview: When the local Burger Joint is being threatened by a rogue Bakugan, Dan steps up to save the day and the burgers!

episodes.name: Monkey See, Monkey Don't
episodes.overview: The AO stop neighborhood kids from copycat behavior (namely, using their Bakugan for frivolous reasons).

episodes.name: Bully for You
episodes.overview: The AO must handle a neighborhood bully who is using his Bakugan to pick on the local kids.

episodes.name: Trolling for Laughs
episodes.overview: Wynton's constant practical jokes wear thin on his Bakugan Trox so the Bakugan decide to teach him a lesson.

episodes.name: Local Heroes
episodes.overview: After the AO cause accidental destruction Dan's parents question whether the kids should be allowed to keep their Bakugan.

episodes.name: Pegatrix
episodes.overview: Lia disagrees with her new Bakugan Pegatrix on battle techniques but during a fierce fight Lia must rely on Pegatrix's battle savy.

episodes.name: Frenemies
episodes.overview: Two new Bakugan Brawlers, Shun and Magnus, try out for the AO.

episodes.name: Strata's Fear
episodes.overview: The AO solve the mystery of a kid's missing Bakugan and meet a Bakugan Hunter named Strata.

episodes.name: Dog Daze
episodes.overview: Lightning discovers a new Bakugan, Artulean, leading to an unhealthy rivalry with Howlkor.

episodes.name: In Focus
episodes.overview: While Lia's newswoman mom does an expose on the AO Strata the Hunter tries to capture Hydorous.

episodes.name: The Exit
episodes.overview: The AO compete with The Exit, a rival Brawling team for ViewTube hits, leading to a "winner take all" brawl.

episodes.name: The Lost and the Cost
episodes.overview: A promotor tries to get the AO to join an official league for Bakugan Battling.

episodes.name: Mr. Moon
episodes.overview: Wynton finds a new Bakugan who proves difficult to control but things get more complicated when Col. Tripp seizes control of Trox.

episodes.name: What's Wrong with Dan?
episodes.overview: With "Dan" behaving strangely toward the AO Lightning sniffs out the truth, an impostor!

episodes.name: Babysitting Bedlam
episodes.overview: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day.

episodes.name: Rubbed the Wrong Way
episodes.overview: Dan and Wynton meet a boy who leads them into a maze where the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

episodes.name: Mask of Power
episodes.overview: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan.

episodes.name: Story Holes
episodes.overview: A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan.

episodes.name: Home on the Run
episodes.overview: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family.

episodes.name: Top Slot
episodes.overview: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats.

episodes.name: Fathers and Friends
episodes.overview: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream.

episodes.name: Midsummer Nightmare
episodes.overview: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

episodes.name: Dawn Before Dusk (1)
episodes.overview: AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become larger.

episodes.name: Dawn Before Dusk (2)
episodes.overview: Benton Dusk reveals AO have been identified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

episodes.name: Stratified
episodes.overview: AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned.

episodes.name: Maze Daze
episodes.overview: The AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

episodes.name: All Jungled Up
episodes.overview: AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko.

episodes.name: Outer Demons
episodes.overview: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining.

episodes.name: Matter of the Mind
episodes.overview: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source.

episodes.name: Core Cell
episodes.overview: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

episodes.name: Subterranean Homesick Blues
episodes.overview: AO return home to learn that no time has passed but they soon discover their knowledge of brawling has gotten years advanced.

episodes.name: Honey Struck
episodes.overview: After Strata is sent packing the AO discover that they have picked up a hitchhiker a Panda-like Bakugan.

episodes.name: Shun Shine
episodes.overview: AO want to evolve their Bakugan like Dan did with Drago but only Shun finds a way by tapping into the energy of the Mind Core Cell.

episodes.name: Ronin Son
episodes.overview: Shun's cousin claims Hydorous as his intellectual property the AO must battle to keep their friend.

episodes.name: Framing Device
episodes.overview: Confronted by China, Riot Lia learns to evolve Pegatrix after realizing the true meaning behind her filming obsession.

episodes.name: Bad Actors
episodes.overview: Dan tries to lie about evolving Drago and gets exposed while the team face off against Duran Dane and his Bakugan.

episodes.name: Tripped Up
episodes.overview: Dan and Wynton stumble on both a possible hidden location and Colonel Tripp who wants the energy source for himself.

episodes.name: Power Tripp
episodes.overview: After a falling out with Dan, Wynton is mind-controlled by Tripp who stages an attack to ignite a war.

episodes.name: A Real Steal
episodes.overview: Dan embarks on a solo adventure to outdo Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers.

episodes.name: Lightning Unleashed
episodes.overview: Lightning uncovers the Mind Core Cell buried beneath the Earth and battles Stata the Hunter in an effort to protect its secret.

episodes.name: The Throw Down
episodes.overview: Lightning reveals his discovery of the Mind Core Cell but the AO arrive only to discover that Magnus has already beaten them to it.

episodes.name: Brawl for It All
episodes.overview: Both team's Bakugan knocked into a hibernation state by the Mind Core Cell!

episodes.name: Career Opportunities
episodes.overview: After defeating Magnus the AO get an offer of employment from a surprising source Philomena Dusk!

episodes.name: Punch the Clock
episodes.overview: During a commercial to celebrate their joining the AAAnimus team Dan and the AO rebel before they sellout.

episodes.name: High Flying Hostiles
episodes.overview: While escorting the Mind Core Cell to AAAnimus Campus the AO are attacked by Masato Kazami and his Body Guards.

episodes.name: Backfire Brawl
episodes.overview: Philomena's attempt to refocus the Mind Core Cell's power backfires and the AO must fight their fellow employees.

episodes.name: Hostile Take Over
episodes.overview: After more unsuccessful attempts to harness Core Cell energy the AO must battle their own Bakugan with AAAnimus tech in order to save them.

episodes.name: The Big Bounce
episodes.overview: The AO confront Philomena with concerns about her control over the Core Cell energy.

episodes.name: Awesome vs. AAAnimus (1)
episodes.overview: The AO plan on sneaking into AAAnimus and rescuing their Bakugan but are stopped by Benton who offers up an alternate plan.

episodes.name: Awesome vs. AAAnimus (2)
episodes.overview: The AO team up with Benton Dusk to recapture their stolen Bakugan and free the energy from the Mind Core Cell.

1.name: Battle Planet
1.overview: Dan Kouzo and his pals bond with mysterious creatures known as Bakugan while fighting sinister forces out to control the world.

episodes.name: The Forbidden Isle
episodes.overview: The AO travel to a remote island in search of a Core Cell, but instead they find the Bakugan known as Kelion, which soon bonds with Dan.

episodes.name: New World Orders
episodes.overview: The AO discover a small group of kids and Bakugan being used as laborers against their will, but freeing them is only half the problem.

episodes.name: In the Wild
episodes.overview: The AO are invited to a video-stars conference, but when the chartered jet goes down, the AO must give over to their wild sides to survive!

episodes.name: Call Me Old Brakken
episodes.overview: Lord Brakken is the ultimate AO super-fan, but his zeal takes a dark turn when he looks to prove that he is their superior in battle.

episodes.name: Hide Matrix and Seek
episodes.overview: The AO go undercover to try and pass as citizens of Lord Brakken, but quickly discover that even minor celebrity makes anonymity impossible.

episodes.name: Or Forever Hold Your Peace
episodes.overview: The AO seek to rescue Lia from an arranged marriage with Lord Brakken only to discover she just made a major discovery for the Bakugan!

episodes.name: Two Sides of the Coin
episodes.overview: The AO and Magnus take parallel tracks to retrieve the same piece of data, one that promises a breakthrough in the Bakugan phenomenon.

episodes.name: The Race for Gold
episodes.overview: When the AO seek out a mythical, lost Bakugan, they get more than they bargained for when Magnus is on the trail of this new discovery, too.

episodes.name: Seek and Hide
episodes.overview: Sent to investigate a Japanese island by Benton Dusk, the AO discover a hidden facility conducting experiments that affect The Hide.

episodes.name: Family First
episodes.overview: Trapped by his father, Shun is forced to battle his own friends, revealing dark secrets about the Kazami family and Masato's experiments.

episodes.name: A Door Closes, a Door Opens
episodes.overview: Shun must stand up to his father and protect his friends before Masato destroys everyone.

episodes.name: Kazami's Gambit
episodes.overview: When Magnus looks to steal the Dimensional Doorway, Shun and Ichiro must make peace with the AO stop the Doorway from destroying them all.

episodes.name: A Devil on Your Shoulder
episodes.overview: Near giving up, Magnus gains new strength and insight on the AO's mission to find Core Cells that will eventually lead him down a dark hole.

episodes.name: Vestral Visions
episodes.overview: Drago's sickness leads Dan to a revelation that there is an ailing Core Cell.

episodes.name: Bakuzoned!
episodes.overview: Strata's return is much more than a simple rematch when he's been infected by a strange ooze.

episodes.name: The Golden Secret
episodes.overview: Using Strata's gauntlet, the AO think they've found a way thorugh the labyrinth, but soon discover trusting the enemy is not always best.

episodes.name: The Bakugan Breakers
episodes.overview: Magnus's new team of Bakugan Brawlers overhear Lightning's warnings of a sick Core Cell and decide to capture the dog to find its location.

episodes.name: The Awful Ones
episodes.overview: Magnus heads into the Labyrinth to claim the Fortus Core Cell for his own, but comes in direct contact with the evil versions of the AO.

episodes.name: The Mask of Pride
episodes.overview: Driven by revenge, Magnus decides to go back into the labyrinth, face the AO and claim the Fortus Core Cell energy for himself.

episodes.name: The Graveyard of Courage
episodes.overview: Super charged by the Fortus Core Cell, Magnus wages war on the AO only to discover his newfound power has a price attached.

episodes.name: Vestroia (1)
episodes.overview: The AO discover the only way to stop Magnus, and possibly save him, involves shutting down the infected Fortus Core Cell./

episodes.name: Vestroia (2)
episodes.overview: The AO must decide whether or not to help Benton Dusk destroy the infected Fortus Core Cell, risking the destruction of their own Bakugan.

episodes.name: Too Much
episodes.overview: The Hide Matrix goes crazy and a simple AO training mission turns into a complicated rampage that brings down Studio D./

episodes.name: Who Are You?
episodes.overview: After the loss of their HQ, the AO is a little off, but in talking to Benton Dusk, they learn a new sense of purpose for their team.

episodes.name: Happy
episodes.overview: The AO expect a fight in Brakistan, but soon discover that old enemies Lord Brakken, Magnus, and Nillious are unnaturally happy to see them.

episodes.name: One Way or Another
episodes.overview: In the heat of emotions, Shun convinces Lord Brakken that his usual enemies are the best allies he has to sequester a renegade Core Cell.

episodes.name: Stormy Weather
episodes.overview: On a flight to their next Core Cell mission, the AO's plane falls under attack by Pyravian, who strangely believes the team to be Bakuzon.

episodes.name: Who Can It Be Now
episodes.overview: The AO find themselves in a battle against the Bakuzon forces of Tiko that upends everything they thought they knew about Core Cells.

episodes.name: In My Room
episodes.overview: When the AO report that they've been fighting the wrong fight, they discover that Benton has been corrupted by the villainous Tiko.

episodes.name: An Army of Their Own
episodes.overview: The AO are forced to turn to Philomena Dusk for help, only to realize that they have led Benton/Tiko right to the AAAnimus Campus.

episodes.name: Calling All Parents
episodes.overview: When the parents of the world are turned against their children and confiscate their Bakugan, the AO must seek out the Rowdy Reds.

episodes.name: Nowhere to Turn
episodes.overview: Nowhere to Turn: While the AO attempt to gain allies and warn other children, Wynton is confronted by Armstrong Tripp, who now works for Benton Dusk.

episodes.name: Girl Power
episodes.overview: When Lia battles with China Riot, they eventually come to an understanding as China finally realizes she's been set up by Benton/Tiko.

episodes.name: Return to the Fold
episodes.overview: On the run and with options dwindling, the AO turn to Shun's father, Ichiro Kazami, for help.

episodes.name: Kazami Family Feud
episodes.overview: Masato attacks, but the AO soon realize that Ichiro is keeping a Golden Bakugan captive, forcing them to choose between the lesser of two evils!

episodes.name: Greatest of the Kazami
episodes.overview: Shun makes an impassioned plea to Ichiro, but it is too late as the Kazami compound is overrun by Bakuzon and the Visvus Cell is lost.

episodes.name: Our Ugly Selves
episodes.overview: Abandoned in the Vestroia Labyrinth, the AO must deal with their personal losses and, worse, the Bakuzoned Awful Ones!

episodes.name: Thryno Lives!
episodes.overview: When the AO and Magnus form an alliance to free the Golden Bakugan, their differences lead to a horrible sacrifice for Dan and Lia.

episodes.name: The Healing Challenge
episodes.overview: As the AO struggle to hold together, a discovery is made involving the Golden Bakugan, a Golden Drome, and curing of a Bakuzoned Gorthion.

episodes.name: The Golden Drome
episodes.overview: While Dan and Drago enter the Golden Drome to heal Trhyno, the rest of the AO defend the Golden Drome from a militia of human hunters.

episodes.name: The Golden Forge
episodes.overview: As Dan and Drago battle to free Trhyno from Tiko's infection, they learn the history of Vestroia and the nature of Golden Bakugan.

episodes.name: A Deep Hibernation
episodes.overview: Trhyno must give Dan and Drago the power they need if they are to have any chance in stopping Tiko from destroying both Vestroia and Earth.

episodes.name: At the Beginning, an Ending
episodes.overview: When Shun and Lia track down Ichiro and Masato on their quest for more allies, they are forced to battle a Bakuzoned Ichiro!

episodes.name: This Late Hour
episodes.overview: Shun, Lia and Masato must square off against the Dusk Forces, but they are not alone when they are joined by Lt. Brenan and Kino.

episodes.name: Bakuzon at the Gate (1)
episodes.overview: As the Dusk Forces storm the Numena Core Cell, infighting between the Awesome Ones and their allies threatens to tear them all apart.

episodes.name: Bakuzon at the Gate (2)
episodes.overview: Tiko/Dusk Forces have coalesced into global power and are waging a no holds barred assault on the Numena Core Cell.

episodes.name: Planet-Ception
episodes.overview: The final showdown between Tiko and AO with the future of Earth and Vestroia in balance.

episodes.name: United We Stand
episodes.overview: The Awesome Ones return home as heroes, wondering what battles await them in the future.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Boy
episodes.overview: After stopping Tiko's rampage, the Awesome Brawlers have become world-famous heroes and Bakugan-mania sweeps the globe. In celebration of the Awesome Brawlers efforts, a tournament is being held in their honor. But the battles are quickly cut short when a rogue brawler and his golden Bakugan crash the event.

episodes.name: A New Power
episodes.overview: A Rogue brawler, Agit and his golden Bakugan have crashed the Awesome Brawlers party. Who is this brawler? How can he control a Golden Bakugan? Only one way to find out - Bakugan Brawl!

episodes.name: Baku-Gear
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers are excited over their discovery of Baku-Gear, and want to get some footage of it in action. While they're filming, an underclassman named Trey challenges Dan to battle. Who will emerge victorious in the impromptu battle?

episodes.name: Bakugan Rock!
episodes.overview: Baku-gear has shown up twice for Dan and Drago and it's starting to eat away at the other awesome brawlers. It's time they take it into their own hands. When Lia and Wynton go up against the rockin' new brawlers in town, they show Dan and Drago that they are not the only one who can summon this cool new tool!

episodes.name: Brawler Headhunting
episodes.overview: As acting president of Kazami International, Shun is called upon to entertain another new young CEO Luca Schmidt, who's interested in doing business with the Kazami International. But Shun quickly realizes something is up when Luca tries woo him over to his brawling team - the Glanz Five.

episodes.name: Lightning's Entrance Exam
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers may be world famous heroes, but that doesn't mean they get out of going to school. They are still regular kids, doing regular kid things. But teachers may have something to say when Lightening decides he wants to join his buddies in the classroom.

episodes.name: Trouble Busters!
episodes.overview: Now that the Awesome Brawlers are world famous Bakugan experts, they want to help people solve their Bakugan-related problems. When the world's quietest town is experiencing unexplained noises, the Awseome Brawlers are called in to get to the bottom of it

episodes.name: French Fry Wars
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers are arguing over who gets to eat the last french-fry. At first, each member makes a case for why they should to be the one to eat it. But the quarrel quickly escalates into trash talk and revealing secrets about one another. With everyone now upset, things take an unexpected turn.

episodes.name: The Phantom Thief Comes to Call
episodes.overview: An archeological discovery is made in Los Volmos. Exploration at the site is cut short, when a master thief and his apprentice attempt to steal the ancient Bakugan artifacts. When the Awesome Brawlers hear the news, they step in to thwart the thieves.

episodes.name: Phantom Thief Ajit
episodes.overview: An Ancient Bakugon artifact from an archeological discovery is placed in the Los Volmos Museum. The Awesome Brawlers are charged with guarding the artifacts from any further attempts thievery.

episodes.name: The Lady and the Queen
episodes.overview: China Riot finds a new Bakugan: Barbetra. But this buzzy new Bakugan is a bit timid on the battleground. Riot takes her on as her new project to turn her into the battle queen she knows she can be.

episodes.name: The AB's Silver Screen Debut
episodes.overview: Lord Brakken and Duran have teamed up and are now the Bakugan film business. They look to the Awesome Brawlers for their expertise in both Bakugan culture and film making to get their movie made!

episodes.name: Nice to Meet You, Bakugan!
episodes.overview: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

episodes.name: Magnus
episodes.overview: After the Tiko incident, Bakugan brawling with a device has become extremely restricted. But there will always be people using devices to control Bakugan for evil. Magnus has taken it upon himself to step in and stop these villains and their wrongdoing.

episodes.name: The Bakugan Battle League
episodes.overview: Benton Dusk is in the process of renovating a state of the art Bakugan Brawling stadium. When it comes to brawling, who better to test out the new arena than the Awesome Brawlers!

episodes.name: The Ancient Elder
episodes.overview: Dan finds a new baku-bud in Gillitar. Well "bud" may be too strong a word, Dan and gang quickly learn that Gillator has a few "quirks" that keep him from fitting in with the rest of the Awesome Brawler's Bakugan.

episodes.name: Bakugan Wynton
episodes.overview: Wynton has a new device that tracks down Bakugan! Right out of the gate the device works and, Wynton meets: Batrix. Like his name, Batrix is a little batty, and these two are certainly in for a "batty" first adventure.

episodes.name: The Boy from Brazil
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers are off to a soccer match! In the process of doing so Shun discovers a new Bakugan friend, the boisterous Ramparian, and a new foe in Brazilian soccer star: Pepe.

episodes.name: Haunted House
episodes.overview: Rumor has it that there's a haunted building in Los Volmos, and the Awesome Brawlers are on the case! Who doesn't like a good ghost hunt, plus capturing a ghost on camera should make Awesome Brawlers' next video a huge success!

episodes.name: Two of a Kind
episodes.overview: Veronica Venegas is doing a special report on the Awesome brawlers own: Lightening! The special report takes a back seat when Lightening is challenged to a brawl. Lightening uses this brawl the perfect opportunity to rollout his new Bakugan partner: Tretorous.

episodes.name: Magnus P.I. (1)
episodes.overview: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself.

episodes.name: Magnus P.I. (2)
episodes.overview: Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan. Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

episodes.name: Awesome Brawlers Training Camp (1)
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned.

episodes.name: Awesome Brawlers Training Camp (2)
episodes.overview: Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

episodes.name: The Bakugan Battle League Begins
episodes.overview: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve.

episodes.name: Riot vs. Ajit
episodes.overview: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

episodes.name: Kung Fu Master
episodes.overview: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!

episodes.name: A Battle of Popularity
episodes.overview: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

episodes.name: The Mysterious Revenger
episodes.overview: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!

episodes.name: Wynton vs. Lia
episodes.overview: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

episodes.name: The Best Friend
episodes.overview: The top four brawlers in the Bakugan Battle League have been decided. For this round of the semi-finals it's a battle of best friends: Wynton vs. Dan. The winner of this battle between best buddies will move on to the championship round.

episodes.name: Thief and Brawler
episodes.overview: In the final battle of the Bakugan Battle league semi-finals it's Shun vs. Ajit. It's a grueling battle of focus, will, and strength, only a true brawler to emerge victorious.

episodes.name: Final Battle! Dan vs. Ajit
episodes.overview: It's time for the event everyone in Los Volmos has been waiting for, The Bakugan Battle League finals! It's the Awesome Brawler's Dan Kouzo vs. the golden Bakugan brawler Ajit, these two face-off in a final brawl for it all.

episodes.name: Secrets Exposed
episodes.overview: The Bakugan Battle League has ended, and the winner has been determined, but the celebration is cut short when Phantom Thief Storm crashes the party by stealing everyone's Bakugan! It's up to Dan and Ajit to stop Storm and return all the stolen Bakugan.

episodes.name: The Director
episodes.overview: Everett Ray reaches out to Lia with an opportunity that seems too good to be true. Everett is now working in show business and proposes to make Lia's dream of becoming a film director come true. He's taken care of all the arrangements; all Lia has to do is provide the directorial vision.

episodes.name: Queen Ebony
episodes.overview: On his daily jaunt, Lightning learns of a street cat named Ebony, who's been treating dogs like servants, threatening them to do her bidding or face the wrath of her Bakugan! Lightning tries to reason with Ebony but when that doesn't work, it turns into a cat vs. dog Bakugan brawl!

episodes.name: Here Comes Haavik
episodes.overview: An evil shapeshifting alien has landed in Los Volmos! If that wasn't bad enough, he has a group of robot mechanoids on his trail trying to bring him justice. Meanwhile, Dan has accepted a battle challenge from a pair of brawlers, Chad and Trey.

episodes.name: The Fusion Bakugan Arrive
episodes.overview: Still humiliated by their defeat, Chad and Trey challenge Dan to rematch but this time they have a few tricks up their sleeve, and a little help on their side.

episodes.name: Sophie, the Bakuganist
episodes.overview: Magnus is on the trail of the illegal Baku-brawling devices and, is looking to cut off the supply at its source. When he witnesses an illegal deal going down, he knows it's up to him to go after the shipment to keep the illegal devices off the street.

episodes.name: Midnight Train Battle!
episodes.overview: Sophie Judson Warfield, a wealthy activist with the Citizens to Save Bakugan Society, is working to put an end to all Bakugan brawling. Her latest target is the Awesome Brawlers themselves. When Wynton doesn't take Sophie seriously, the encounter quickly turns into an all-out Bakugan brawl.

episodes.name: Dangerous Dealings
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawler's have become aware of a growing number of adults with illegal Baku-brawling devices. But where are they all coming from? Shun decides to take things into his own hands and sets up a "sting" operation to try to draw out the person selling the devices.

episodes.name: The Hunter Returns
episodes.overview: Lightning has been caught and locked up by an overly aggressive dog catcher! And to make things worse, he doesn't have his collar with Baku-balls. At the compound where he's being held, he runs into an old foe. It's up to these two enemies to team up and escape their captor.

episodes.name: Farewell, Phantom Thief (1)
episodes.overview: After being exposed as a phantom thief in the Bakugan battle league, the Awesome Brawlers are concerned about Ajit, but have no idea of his whereabouts. Dan is particularly affected by Ajit's disappearance and sets out to find him to get some answers.

episodes.name: Farewell, Phantom Thief (2)
episodes.overview: Ajit is out to set right all the wrong doings of his phantom thief past. When he attempts to break into a museum to return artifacts, his mentor Storm is waiting for him. A Bakugan brawl breaks out between two when Storm rolls out his new Bakugan: Cimoga.

episodes.name: The Awesome Brawlers and Haavik
episodes.overview: It's the Haavik Show! Haavik shows up unexpectedly at the practice field and proposes he and Dan play a little game. The Awesome Brawlers have never seen this man before, but they sense something is odd about him. Regardless, when Haavik strokes Dan's ego, there's no way he's backing down from this challenge.

episodes.name: First Fusion! Drago and Tretorous
episodes.overview: With his back against the wall, Dan tries flipping the script on Haavik by challenging him to a game of his own - a Bakugan Brawl. If Dan wins, then Haavik will have to set him, and the other Awesome Brawler's free.

episodes.name: The Puppet Awesome Brawlers
episodes.overview: The Awesome brawlers go to see Benton Dusk to tell him about the Fusion Bakugan and ask him if he knows anything about this character: Haavik. However, the meeting takes an unexpected twist when Haavik decides to crash it.

episodes.name: The Return of Sophie
episodes.overview: A video has surfaced showing Toshi using an illegal Baku-Brawling device! Shun has his hands full when Sophie starts making trouble for Kazami Holdings, accusing them of illegally exploiting Bakugan.

episodes.name: Wynton's Reality Show
episodes.overview: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!

episodes.name: Bakugan Soccer
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

episodes.name: Shun and Lightning
episodes.overview: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings.

episodes.name: Premonition of a Storm
episodes.overview: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped! Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

episodes.name: Superstar Dan
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawler's head to Tokyo for the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition. While Wynton, Shun, Lia and Lightning see the sites, and enjoy the tastes of Japan, Dan, as the Los Volmos Champion, has official Bakugan Battle League duties and obligations that keep him busy.

episodes.name: Awesome Brawlers on Vacation
episodes.overview: Lia, Lightning, Shun and Wynton explore the sights of Toyko when a rogue Bakugan shows up and rampages. The Awesome Brawlers have to spring into action, rolling out their Bakugan to stop the rogue enemy before any real damage can be done.

episodes.name: Bakugan Battle League, Tokyo Edition
episodes.overview: It's the start of the Bakugan Battle League - Toyko edition! The first round will be a Battle Royale style competition, where only half the competitors will make it through to the next round. Along with the Awesome brawlers the field of competitors is filled with familiar friends and foes.

episodes.name: Battle Royal
episodes.overview: The first round of the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo edition continues. The Awesome Brawler's and their Bakugan battle their way through the challenge and face off against tough competitors.

episodes.name: The Second Stage Begins
episodes.overview: With half of the brawlers eliminated, the second stage of the Bakugan Battle league begins. This round will be a timed race to the finish, with all kinds of tricks and traps that will slow down even the best brawlers.

episodes.name: Mechanoids Attack!
episodes.overview: Mechanoids have crashed the second stage of the Bakugan Battle League, causing all kinds of havoc. The Awesome Brawlers will now have to race against the clock, battling competitors and mechanoids if they want to make it through this round.

episodes.name: The Other Fight (1)
episodes.overview: Eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League, Ajit is airlifted by drone to a massive cargo ship in the middle of Tokyo Bay. Now that he's on board the cargo ship, he must rescue Dan and Drago, and stop whoever is sabotaging the Battle League.

episodes.name: The Other Fight (2)
episodes.overview: Dan and Ajit investigate the mysterious cargo ship that the eliminated Brawlers and Bakugan are being held on. Dan races to track down Drago, but along the way runs into a familiar face.

episodes.name: The Bakugan Battle League Dash
episodes.overview: With Dan and Ajit eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition, the remaining Awesome Brawlers - Shun, Wynton, Lia and Lightning race to complete the second stage of the competition. In order to make it to the final stage, the gang will have to pull together to defeat some tough competition.

episodes.name: The Final Stage
episodes.overview: It's the final stage of the Bakugan Battle League Tokyo Edition! The remaining Awesome Brawlers are ready to go, but just as the final round begins, the competitors are surprised with some unwelcome guests.

episodes.name: The Tokyo Catastrophe
episodes.overview: Haavik has highjacked the Bakugan Battle league - Tokyo Edition! He's been using the tournament as a platform for his sinister plot to bring chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo.

episodes.name: Bakugan Battle League Finale
episodes.overview: Haavik unleashes an army of unruly Bakugan to bring his own brand of chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo. It's all hands-on-deck to stop the invasion, and foil Haavik's plot.

episodes.name: Champion of the Universe, Dan!
episodes.overview: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all.

episodes.name: Operation Babysitter
episodes.overview: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

episodes.name: Beastie Team Battle
episodes.overview: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend.

episodes.name: Ajit and Lia
episodes.overview: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

episodes.name: Once More into the Maze
episodes.overview: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate.

episodes.name: Grandpas in the Wild
episodes.overview: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

episodes.name: The Past Revealed
episodes.overview: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!

episodes.name: Run! A Storm's on the Way
episodes.overview: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

episodes.name: Golden Bakugan Encounter
episodes.overview: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ.

episodes.name: Ties of Gold
episodes.overview: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

episodes.name: Nightmare
episodes.overview: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning. It turns out, Dan's dreams have been hijacked by Haavik, who's trying to spread his vision of chaos and destruction to Dan!

episodes.name: Bad Dan
episodes.overview: Haavik has taken control of Dan and sends him on a Bakugan rampage! With "Bad Dan" causing all kinds of havoc and destruction, the rest of the Awesome Brawlers have no choice but to roll out to try to contain "Bad Dan".

episodes.name: Dusk Industries Under Attack
episodes.overview: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction.

episodes.name: Taking Dan Back
episodes.overview: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

episodes.name: Who's the Fake?!
episodes.overview: With the reveal that Haavik is a shapeshifting Alien, the ABs start to get super-paranoid, realizing that ANYONE could be Haavik in disguise. The suspicion quickly turns inward, and the ABs are left wondering if they have an imposter among them!

episodes.name: Trouble Busters! 2
episodes.overview: A kid brawler named Oliver has lost his Bakugan! This seems like a job for the Trouble Busters. The Awesome Brawlers help him chase down and try to catch the elusive Bakugan, who leads them on a wild goose chase through Los Volmos.

episodes.name: Bakugan Battle Circus
episodes.overview: Shun and Dan head to the Bakugan circus for a little fun, but the fun is interrupted when the star Bakugan are too exhausted to perform. Shun and Dan know the show must go on, and step in to lend a hand. Things go as planned until the evil Ringleader attempts to bring down the big top performance.

episodes.name: Ebony Manor
episodes.overview: Lightning reunites with an old frenemy - Ebony. This time the kitty queen of the streets has a new home and is living a life of luxury with her new master.

episodes.name: Everett's Trap
episodes.overview: Shun and Masato head to Tokyo's Battle Island to discuss plans for hosting public Bakugan battles. Upon landing, they quickly learn it's a set up! The two are now stranded and faced with heaps of brawlers, who are all looking to bring them down!

episodes.name: Kazami vs. Mc Q
episodes.overview: Shun and Masato manage to fend off a horde of brawlers on Battle Island, but they quickly learn that was only a diversion- one of Kazami's research centers is under siege. The two must find a way off the island and head off to defend the research center.

episodes.name: The Awesome Burger Brawl
episodes.overview: The Burger Joint is hosting a hamburger eating contest to promote their new Bakugan themed burger! The contest gets underway without a hitch, that is until Sophie and the Bakugan Preservation Society crash the event with a bakugan brawl!

episodes.name: Master and Apprentice
episodes.overview: A wealthy man, Mr. Gold, has duped Storm and Ajit, and trapped them in his personal prison. But no prison can hold the cunning phantom thief Storm and his former apprentice, Ajit for long.

episodes.name: Bakugan Uproar
episodes.overview: While the Awesome Brawlers' Bakugan squabble about what to watch on TV at Studio D, Haavik unleashes his newly created five-faction fusion Bakugan: Sabrus on the city of Los Volmos.

episodes.name: The Fusion Bakugan Sabrus
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers are in pursuit of Haavik and his new Bakugan, Sabrus but all they can find is the trail of destruction that Sabrus has left behind. They need to figure out where Haavik and his Bakugan will strike next and put an end to his rampage.

episodes.name: Ancient Golden Bakugan Garillion
episodes.overview: The ancient golden Bakugan, Garillion Infinity has come to Los Volmos to try to put an end to Haavik's show of destruction and chaos but upon arriving he turns his sights on Drago, Dan and the Awesome Brawlers.

episodes.name: The Name of Infinity
episodes.overview: Haavik and his five-faction fusion Bakugan Sabrus take their rampage to AAAnimus' headquarters. The Awesome Brawlers quickly track down the rampaging duo and face off!

episodes.name: In the Darkness
episodes.overview: An encounter with Storm and his trick rose leaves Magnus temporarily blinded and unable to brawl. With the help of an unlikely partner, Magnus pursues Storm in an attempt to defeat him and restore his vision.

episodes.name: Indecisive Emily
episodes.overview: Emily obtains a second Bakugan named Chrissy. It's soon obvious that Emily is having trouble brawling with both Chrissy and Webam, and it's up to Dan, Drago and Gillator to teach them how to brawl as a team.

episodes.name: The Eclipse
episodes.overview: There's an eclipse happening over Los Volmos, but there's something even more strange going on. Dan and Drago quickly realize something's up; no one seems like themselves today. The two need to get to the bottom of it and return things back to normal.

episodes.name: Follow Haavik!
episodes.overview: Magnus and Ajit spot Haavik on the street and decide to follow him, but the shape shifting Haavik is on to them. It's not long before an epic brawl breaks out between them - Five Faction Fusion Sabrus vs. Nillious X Darkus and Pharol.

episodes.name: Tiko's Back?!
episodes.overview: In order to make Sabrus a 6 faction fusion Bakugan, Haavik heads into the maze to try to capture a golden Bakugan who has brought "mayhem and destruction" to Earth once before - Tiko!

episodes.name: Arise, Ultimate Infinity!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers manage to thwart Haavik's attempt to fuse Tiko with Sabrus, but Haavik ends up escaping with the golden Bakugan, Pyravian. Now the Awesome Brawlers must track down Haavik before he can form his ultimate 6 faction fusion Bakugan.

episodes.name: The AB Bakugan Battle League! (1)
episodes.overview: With all the mayhem and destruction Haavik is causing, the Awesome Brawlers decide that a bit of Bakugan brawling is the perfect distraction to take their minds off all the trouble. With the help of some friends, they start the Awesome Brawler Bakugan Battle league!

episodes.name: The AB Bakugan Battle League! (2)
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawler's Bakugan Battle league rages on. Just as the semifinal round comes to a close, an uninvited guest crashes the party, bringing an alarming end to the battle league.

episodes.name: Haavik's Challenge
episodes.overview: Haavik has crashed the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan League, and challenges the Awesome Brawlers in a battle league of his own!

episodes.name: Storm Haavik's Tower
episodes.overview: In order to keep Earth and Vestroia safe and rescue Drago, the Awesome Brawlers agree to enter Haavik's Bakugan Battle League, and race toward Haavik's tower for the final showdown.

episodes.name: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik
episodes.overview: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins.

episodes.name: Their Fights
episodes.overview: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

episodes.name: Haavik's Final Show
episodes.overview: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!

episodes.name: Miracle Planet
episodes.overview: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

episodes.name: Drago Returns!
episodes.overview: After healing in Vestroia, Drago makes a heroic return.

episodes.name: The Bakugan of Junk Island
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers must face off against some strange new Bakugan.

episodes.name: Lia and Fenneca
episodes.overview: Lia and her new Bakugan quickly learn one another's moves after an old enemy appears.

episodes.name: Lightning and Ferascal
episodes.overview: A mysterious psychic takes an interest in the new Bakugan.

episodes.name: A Former Thief and a Laid Back Dude
episodes.overview: A Bakugan hunter quickly attacks Ajit, Lia and Lightning.

episodes.name: My Name Is Sharktar
episodes.overview: McQ wants to get his hands on the new Kazami tech, but Shun and Sharktar stand in his way.

episodes.name: Wynton's Friend
episodes.overview: A new girl takes a liking to Wynton, but his new Bakugan is suspicious about her motives.

episodes.name: Magnus Returns!
episodes.overview: Strata tries to force Emily into a Bakugan Brawl for fun.

episodes.name: Gregorius Reed Arrives
episodes.overview: After hearing from Pyravian, the Awesome Brawlers try to track down a stolen core cell.

episodes.name: A Mysterious Bakugan
episodes.overview: The hunt sends the crew to the estate of a wealthy collector.

episodes.name: The Search for Geogan!
episodes.overview: Everyone looks for the mysterious Geogan that appeared the night before.

episodes.name: The Geogan Arcleon!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers help recover for a recently hijacked airship.

episodes.name: Chase the Mysterious Bakugan!
episodes.overview: A rogue Bakugan destroys people's property at night, and only the Brawlers can stop it.

episodes.name: Drago in the Crosshairs!
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago face off against a strange golden Bakugan.

episodes.name: Magnus of the Wild
episodes.overview: A returning Magnus readies to battle Dan and the crew.

episodes.name: Gate Card, Set!
episodes.overview: Wynton puts the finishing touches on some new tech, but trouble may ruin the test run.

episodes.name: Supreme Council Calculations
episodes.overview: After arriving in Vestroia, the gang gets some bad news.

episodes.name: Drago's Challenge
episodes.overview: To join the Supreme Council, Drago must prove his worth and battle a golden Bakugan.

episodes.name: Drago Joins the Supreme Council
episodes.overview: A brawl breaks out after Lightning and Ferascal upset a Bakugan.

episodes.name: Find the Triplets!
episodes.overview: The Rowdy Reds run with a rough crowd, so the Brawlers try to bring them back home.

episodes.name: Butt Out of the Bakugan Show!
episodes.overview: The Brawlers compete in the first-ever Exciting Bakugan Spectacular.

episodes.name: Crystal Blue the Songstres
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago duke it out during a rock concert finale.

episodes.name: Magnus's Journey
episodes.overview: Magnus stumbles on a tribe of Cubbo being attacked by a vicious Bakugan.

episodes.name: Beach Battle
episodes.overview: Shun doesn't know how to swim, so the team heads to the beach to teach him.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Masked Bandits!
episodes.overview: Wynton detects strange energy spikes coming from somewhere in Los Volmos.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Brawler!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers are called to face off against the notorious Mad Masks.

episodes.name: Princess of the Garbage Heap, Bethany!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers upset a princess and her Bakugan at the garbage dump.

episodes.name: Find the Mysterious Cryptid, Wolfman!
episodes.overview: The friends head into the wilderness to catch a glimpse of the Wolfman!

episodes.name: The Mascot Cat!
episodes.overview: Lightning meets an old foe at a new sushi restaurant.

episodes.name: The AB's Grand Adventure!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers try their luck with the new Medieval Adventure game at the Coliseum.

episodes.name: The Taste of Memories
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers battle Crystal Blue over the last bag of lentils.

episodes.name: Virtual Brawl
episodes.overview: Benton Dusk brings his virtual reality simulator to help train the Brawlers.

episodes.name: Volcanic Island S.O.S!
episodes.overview: A volcanic eruption cuts the Brawlers' island training session short.

episodes.name: Panic in Pin Point Park
episodes.overview: Wynton brings his younger siblings to a Bakugan arena — and regrets it.

episodes.name: Underground Panic
episodes.overview: The Brawlers battle in one of the deepest, darkest mines in the world.

episodes.name: We Are the EXIT!
episodes.overview: A rival team tries to clean up its image and asks the Brawlers for help.

episodes.name: The Battle Judgement Begins!
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers arrive in Auropolis to decide the fate of Earth and Vestroia.

episodes.name: Viloch Takes the Lead!
episodes.overview: Viloch and Reed clash with Ajit and Pincitaur as the battle begins.

episodes.name: The Battle of Aquilia
episodes.overview: Shun and Sharktar go head-to-head with old rival McQ in the Aquos realm.

episodes.name: The Aquilia Artifact
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago scramble to find crucial artifacts before their battle.

episodes.name: Wynton vs. Magnus
episodes.overview: Dismissive Magnus prompts Wynton to show his fighting strength.

episodes.name: Ventana Adventure
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago endure a grueling race through Ventana to obtain the Ventus artifact.

episodes.name: The Battle of Haora!
episodes.overview: The Battle Judgement moves to Haora, where Dan and Drago want to finish their battle quickly.

episodes.name: Chase the Haora Artifact!
episodes.overview: Sharktar and Shun fight challengers Oxidox and Everett.

episodes.name: True Power
episodes.overview: The Awesome Brawlers worry about their missing teammates as the tournament proceeds to Darkavia.

episodes.name: Showdown in Darkavia!
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago head inside Darkavia’s black caverns.

episodes.name: The Trial of Pyrule
episodes.overview: Dan and a very weak Drago continue the quest for the final artifact in Pyrule.

episodes.name: Passing Through Darkness
episodes.overview: With his power restored, Drago returns to Darkavia for the next brawl.

episodes.name: The Fateful Final Battle!
episodes.overview: It all comes down to the final brawl of the Battle Judgement tournament.

episodes.name: Invincible Viloch
episodes.overview: Old rivals Dan and Magnus face off in an epic fight to the finish.

episodes.name: Geo-Forge Drago!
episodes.overview: Everything's on the line in a colossal showdown between Ultimate Viloch and Geo-Forge Drago!

episodes.name: At the End of the Fight...
episodes.overview: The victor will decide the fate of Earth and Vestroia.

4.name: Geogan Rising
4.overview: The Awesome Brawlers band together to fight off a powerful enemy determined to break the bond between Earth and Vestroia, the Bakugan's home planet.

episodes.name: Bakugan Academy!
episodes.overview: The team meets a fresh class of brawlers at a new training academy.

episodes.name: Roommates
episodes.overview: Dan and the others find out their roommate assignments at the dorms.

episodes.name: Lia and Riot!
episodes.overview: Lia and Riot work together to battle their pesky classmates.

episodes.name: Lightning's Place
episodes.overview: Lightning breaks the school's rules while finding the perfect spot to sleep.

episodes.name: Let's Ace a Difficult Subject!
episodes.overview: Ajit needs some extra help if he wants to pass his strategy class.

episodes.name: A New Studio D Is Born
episodes.overview: The Brawlers search for a place on campus to rebuild their old studio.

episodes.name: Magnus Is Back!
episodes.overview: Magnus returns as the academy's new instructor and challenges Dan to a brawl.

episodes.name: Athena's Wish
episodes.overview: Top student Athena shows off her skills during a showdown with Dan.

episodes.name: A Superstar Returns?!
episodes.overview: Cubbo goes viral online and needs the Brawlers' help to hide from his fans.

episodes.name: The Gate Crushers
episodes.overview: The Brawlers try to stop a new squad from shutting off elemental energy.

episodes.name: Lia and Athena
episodes.overview: Lia asks Athena for help with some strength training.

episodes.name: Field Training
episodes.overview: A Bakugan with excess elemental energy runs wild throughout Los Volmos.

episodes.name: Drago vs. Falcron!
episodes.overview: Falcron must defend the Brawlers from his fellow Bakugan.

episodes.name: Watch Out for Our Rivals
episodes.overview: Wynton's research finds that the number of elemental Bakugan is growing rapidly.

episodes.name: New Heroes Appear?!
episodes.overview: Dan and Wynton face off with colorful new troublemakers in Los Volmos.

episodes.name: Dan vs. Mr. Magnus
episodes.overview: Dan attempts to train the crew with a new elemental evolution.

episodes.name: The Mysterious Marauder
episodes.overview: Masato recruits Shun to investigate a series of attacks at a Kazami factory.

episodes.name: Suspicious Hackett
episodes.overview: The Brawlers suspect that Hackett is up to her old tricks.

episodes.name: Evolutions Unleashed! (1)
episodes.overview: It's Awesome vs. Elemental!

episodes.name: Evolutions Unleashed! (2)
episodes.overview: When a new crew of Baku-brawlers lands in Los Volmos, Dan and the rest of the squad get help battling unfamiliar powers.

episodes.name: The Bakuganist Is Back
episodes.overview: Sophie returns right before an exhibition battle at the Bakugan festival.

episodes.name: Trox Evolution!
episodes.overview: Wynton tries to help Trox evolve with his elemental powers.

episodes.name: A New Power Nano-Gear
episodes.overview: Dan and Drago try to locate who has been training others to evolve from the shadows.

episodes.name: Who's the Real Culprit?!
episodes.overview: The mysterious culprit might be closer than everyone thinks.

episodes.name: Faustus' Secret Revealed
episodes.overview: The Brawlers collect the clues that lead to a surprising suspect causing the trouble.

episodes.name: Clash! Dan vs. Athena
episodes.overview: Dan and Athena clash over the truth about Mr. Faustus.

episodes.name: Truth
episodes.overview: Athena and the Brawlers agree to take down the academy's evil mastermind.

episodes.name: The Battle With Wrath
episodes.overview: Elemental energy makes Wrath an even more powerful Bakugan.

episodes.name: Rebuilding the Academy
